<h1 class="main" itemprop="name">
How to Write Press Release Headlines That Will Get a Journalist‚Äôs Attention
</h1>
<div class="blog-author blog-single-author">
<div class="blog-author-container">
<div class="blog-author-image">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/74c918ac779b81d2a20b9506db75fa23?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/74c918ac779b81d2a20b9506db75fa23?s=192&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='96' loading='lazy' /> </div>
<span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><span itemprop="name"><a href="https://coschedule.com/blog/author/lizzie-davey/" rel="author"><h5>Lizzie Davey</h5></a></span></span>
</div>
<h6 class="category"><span itemprop="articleSection"><a href="https://coschedule.com/topic/content-marketing/" rel="category tag">Content</a></span></h6>
</div>

<div class="blog-cta ha-cta aj-ha-cta">
<img src="https://coschedule.com/blog/wp-content/themes/CoS4/img/headline-analyzer-logo.png" class="ha-logo" alt="Headline Analyzer" />
<h4 class="no-marg">Headline Analyzer</h4>
<p>The blog post headline analyzer will score your overall headline quality and rate its ability to result in social shares, increased traffic, and SEO&nbsp;value.</p>
<a href="/headline-analyzer" target="_blank" title="Check out the Headline Analyzer" class="kmq-blog-post-ha-link">Test every headline before you publish. Try the Headline Analyzer &#187;</a>
</div>

<div class="blog-single-body" itemprop="articleBody">
<p><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-95043 size-full" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headlines.png" alt="How to Write Press Release Headlines That Will Get a Journalist‚Äôs Attention" width="1360" height="570" srcset="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headlines.png 1360w, https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headlines-300x126.png 300w, https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headlines-770x323.png 770w, https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headlines-768x322.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px" /></p>
<p>A press release is great for sharing your latest news with journalists.</p>
<p>Short, snappy overviews and punchy rundowns give your brand the attention it deserves; however, when it comes to shopping your release around, it‚Äôs a numbers game. The more people who read your press release, the higher the chance it will get placed in a good-fit publication.</p>
<p>There‚Äôs no better way to get more eyeballs on your press releases than a well-written headline ‚Äî it‚Äôs the first thing journalists see. If it‚Äôs dull and dry, they‚Äôre not going to click through to read the full release. In fact, they might even delete it.</p>
<p>Avoid this by writing headlines that tell journalists and editors what they need to know in a way that‚Äôs actually interesting and engaging.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs how to do that.</p>
<h2>Get Journalists&#8217; Attention with these Press Release Templates</h2>
<p>When you submit your press release to news outlets, you need to be sure that your formatting can be easily understood and will not be off-putting to the people you rely on to share it ‚Äî journalists. These templates will ensure your content finds its way into the hands of journalists, and that they won&#8217;t hesitate to share it.</p>


