<p><a name="Step 1"></a></p>
<h2>Step 1: Identify Your Topic</h2>
<p>Journalists receive hundreds of press releases each week. Your ultimate goal is to stand out in their overflowing inbox, which is not an easy task ‚Äî especially if you‚Äôre not one-hundred-percent sure what your press release is about.</p>
<p>Before you even <span style="font-style: italic;">think </span>about putting pen to paper or fingers to keyboard, it‚Äôs important to identify your topic.</p>
<p>Not only will this help you create a succinct headline that gets all the information across in a split-second, but it will help you determine other parts of writing and <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://coschedule.com/blog/pr-calendar-template/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">distributing a press release</a></span>, like which journalists to target and which publications are a good fit.</p>
<p>There‚Äôs a good chance your press release is about one thing in particular. It might be the launch of a new feature, a virtual event you‚Äôre running, or the hiring of a new member of staff.</p>
<p>NASA‚Äôs press release headline centers around the main topic: their upcoming news conference.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/102e57df-d333-48ad-9263-9985a1bdb35b_pasted20image200.png" alt="NASA to Host News Conference on Discovery Beyond Our Solar System" width="1264" height="466" /></p>
<p>Your topic should form the foundation of your press release headline. Without it, journalists will be confused and won‚Äôt know what message you‚Äôre trying to get across.</p>
<p>If your press release encompasses a number of different topics, it helps to consolidate those ‚Äî especially when it comes to your headline. This should focus on <span style="font-style: italic;">one </span>element to avoid journalists scratching their heads and automatically resigning your release to their inbox bin.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pro tip:</span>¬†start by listing out everything you want to include in your press release and rank them in a hierarchy of importance. One element is likely to be the most important or the most interesting ‚Äî run with this one in your headline.</p>
<div class='tm-tweet-clear'></div>
<div class='tm-click-to-tweet'>
<div class='tm-ctt-text'><a href='https://twitter.com/share?text=List+out+everything+you+want+to+include+in+your+press+release+and+rank+them+in+a+hierarchy+of+importance.+One+element+is+likely+to+be+the+most+important+or+the+most+interesting+%E2%80%94+run+with+this+one+in+your+headline.&#038;via=coschedule&#038;related=coschedule&#038;url=https://coschedule.com/blog/press-release-headlines/' target='_blank'>List out everything you want to include in your press release and rank them in a hierarchy of importance. One element is likely to be the most important or the most interesting ‚Äî run with this one in your headline.</a></div>
<p><a href='https://twitter.com/share?text=List+out+everything+you+want+to+include+in+your+press+release+and+rank+them+in+a+hierarchy+of+importance.+One+element+is+likely+to+be+the+most+important+or+the+most+interesting+%E2%80%94+run+with+this+one+in+your+headline.&#038;via=coschedule&#038;related=coschedule&#038;url=https://coschedule.com/blog/press-release-headlines/' target='_blank' class='tm-ctt-btn'>Click To Tweet</a></p>
<div class='tm-ctt-tip'></div>
</div>
<p>The easiest way to do this is to simply ask yourself, ‚ÄúWhat am I writing about?‚Äù When you can answer that, you can move on to the next step.</p>
<div class="link-callout"><strong><a href="#toc">Back to the Top</a></strong></div>
<p><a name="Step 2"></a></p>
<h2>Step 2: Identify a Unique Angle</h2>
<p>Every bit of news is exciting for you because it‚Äôs <span style="font-style: italic;">your </span>business, but that doesn‚Äôt mean it will be immediately exciting for journalists and the general public. This is where your headline swoops in to bridge the gap. The idea is to identify a unique angle you can run with that benefits both your business and<span style="font-style: italic;">¬†</span>gives something back to the audience.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-95044 size-full" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headline-questions.png" alt="Press Release Headlines, &quot;Ask yourself the following questions:&quot;" width="1360" height="640" srcset="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headline-questions.png 1360w, https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headline-questions-300x141.png 300w, https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headline-questions-770x362.png 770w, https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/press-release-headline-questions-768x361.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px" /></p>
<p>It‚Äôs difficult to find a completely unique angle to promote ‚Äî especially in competitive industries that always have their fingers on the pulse.</p>
<p>Take some time to consider what makes <span style="font-style: italic;">your </span>story stand out. Is it because your brand is the oldest in the industry? Is it because you‚Äôve interviewed a well-known public figure about an otherwise common topic?</p>
<p>This press release from Dunkin‚Äô Donuts stands out because they‚Äôre the first brand to use this specific feature.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/8e437225-5abd-4762-9120-033b892b702d_pasted20image200.png" alt="From Car to coffee Quicker Than Ever: Dunkin' Donuts is First Brand to Launch Waze's &quot;Order Ahead&quot; Feature" width="834" height="432" /></p>
<p>How can you summarize that story in one headline and one paragraph?</p>
<p>This is where it gets tricky.</p>
<p>Trying to distill your main message into a single sentence is like trying to stuff a round peg in a square hole. A good way to look at it is to think about what information readers need to know right away.<span style="font-style: italic;">¬†</span></p>
<p>This press release headline promotes a new study and picks out a key finding from the study that readers will find particularly compelling. <img src="undefined" alt="" /></p>
<div class="link-callout"><strong><a href="#toc">Back to the Top</a></strong></div>
<p><a name="Step 3"></a></p>
<h2>Step 3: Write Tons of Options for Your Headline</h2>
<p>No one ever writes their best headline the first time around.</p>
<p>In fact, it can take 20 or more tries until you start getting anywhere remotely close to something that will grab attention and pique journalists‚Äô interests.</p>
<div class='tm-tweet-clear'></div>
<div class='tm-click-to-tweet'>
<div class='tm-ctt-text'><a href='https://twitter.com/share?text=It+can+take+20+or+more+tries+until+you+start+getting+anywhere+remotely+close+to+something+that+will+grab+attention+and+pique+journalists%E2%80%99+interests.&#038;via=coschedule&#038;related=coschedule&#038;url=https://coschedule.com/blog/press-release-headlines/' target='_blank'>It can take 20 or more tries until you start getting anywhere remotely close to something that will grab attention and pique journalists‚Äô interests.</a></div>
<p><a href='https://twitter.com/share?text=It+can+take+20+or+more+tries+until+you+start+getting+anywhere+remotely+close+to+something+that+will+grab+attention+and+pique+journalists%E2%80%99+interests.&#038;via=coschedule&#038;related=coschedule&#038;url=https://coschedule.com/blog/press-release-headlines/' target='_blank' class='tm-ctt-btn'>Click To Tweet</a></p>
<div class='tm-ctt-tip'></div>
</div>
<p>Open up a document and start typing.</p>
<p>Jot down anything that comes to mind, but remember to incorporate some of these headline writing tactics:</p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Infuse your headlines with emotional language:</span>¬†Use power words to encourage a specific feeling and drive action.</li>
<li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pay attention to structure and tone:</span>¬†Make sure your headlines make sense and are imbued with the right tone. It also helps to read them aloud.</li>
<li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Adhere to an AP style: </span>Keep on journalists‚Äô good sides by sticking to the grammar style in which they‚Äôre most familiar.</li>
</ul>
<p>Once you‚Äôve got a huge list of headlines to work with, you can start putting them through <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://coschedule.com/headline-analyzer" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CoSchedule‚Äôs Headline Analyzer Studio</a></span>.</p>
<p>Doing this will give you quick insights into the <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://coschedule.com/blog/how-to-write-the-best-headlines-that-will-increase-traffic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">headlines that will work best</a></span>. The tool gives you a score out of 100 and marks you down for using common, unengaging vocabulary.</p>
<div class="link-callout"><strong>Recommended Reading:</strong> <a href="https://coschedule.com/blog/how-to-boost-your-score-in-headline-studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">How to Boost Your Headline Score Using Premium Features in Headline Studio</a></div>
<p>This is what it looks like in action:</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/9a8f549a-bac5-4e75-9440-10bcbdad71a1_Screenshot202021-02-0820at2010.35.45.png" alt="Headline Analyzer Studio: iPad Launch Day Headlines" width="1600" height="856" /></p>
<p>You‚Äôre able to quickly compare the scores of each headline, side-by-side, to see which one comes out on top.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/5a4b5b63-a003-4c89-b9c0-b4135586800b_Screenshot202021-02-0820at2010.36.15.png" alt="Headline Analyzer Studio Word Balance" width="1558" height="1312" /></p>
<p>You‚Äôll then be able to get a breakdown of each headline, including the number of emotional and power words included. Here, at CoSchedule, we try to shoot for scores over 70.</p>
<div class="link-callout"><strong>Recommended Reading:</strong> <a href="https://coschedule.com/blog/emotional-headlines/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">How to Write Emotional Headlines That Get More Shares</a></div>
<p>Play around with your headline ideas and try to create a headline that gets the highest score possible.</p>
<div class="link-callout"><strong><a href="#toc">Back to the Top</a></strong></div>
<p><a name="Step 4"></a></p>
<h2>Step 4: Pick a Winner</h2>
<p>At this point, you should have some strong headline contenders.</p>
<p>Not only will you have a document packed full of headlines focused on the right topic, you‚Äôll also have a better understanding of why<span style="font-style: italic;">¬†</span>people might be interested in your press release.</p>
<p>Finally, after running your best set of headlines through CoSchedule‚Äôs Headline Analyzer Studio, you‚Äôll have several frontrunners that have returned a good score and have a decent amount of emotional, uncommon, and power words.</p>
<p>Now it‚Äôs time to pick your winner.</p>
<p>Wait a second though. You shouldn‚Äôt just go straight for the headline with the highest score. You want to choose one that has a healthy mix of emotional words and<span style="font-style: italic;">¬†</span>conveys the main topic and message of your press release.</p>
<div class="link-callout"><strong><a href="#toc">Back to the Top</a></strong></div>
<p><a name="Step 5"></a></p>
<h2>Step 5: Write the Rest of Your Press Release</h2>
<p>Your headline will now drive the rest of your press release.</p>
<p>Once you‚Äôve nailed the topic and considered how you‚Äôll make your release stand out, you can start crafting the body of it.</p>
<p>Keep your release structured and ensure each paragraph continues to hammer home the topic and the end goal. While emotional and power words don‚Äôt have as much of a place in the body of a press release, you can still use creative language to get your point across.</p>
<p>Check out our <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://coschedule.com/blog/how-to-write-press-releases-examples-templates/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">guide to writing press releases</a></span>, which¬†features several templates you can plug and play with right away.</p>
<div class="link-callout"><strong><a href="#toc">Back to the Top</a></strong></div>
<p><a name="examples"></a></p>
<h2>Examples of the Best Press Release Headlines</h2>
<p>We‚Äôve pulled some real-life <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://coschedule.com/blog/public-relations-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">press release examples</a></span>¬†to show you what‚Äôs possible with a good headline.</p>
<h3>1. DASCOIN launch first fashion blockchain project on top of the Eiffel Tower</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/6915c2d0-e323-4e5d-8878-5eb917832b7d_pasted20image200.png" alt="DASCOIN launch first fashion blockchain project on top of the Eiffel Tower" width="648" height="421" /></p>
<p>There are many things that make this headline stand out. Not only is DASCOIN the ‚Äúfirst‚Äù to do something ‚Äî which makes sure their story stands out ‚Äî but it includes a quirky, but familiar, location.</p>
<p>Who doesn‚Äôt<span style="font-style: italic;">¬†</span>want to read about a project launching at the top of the Eiffel Tower?</p>
<h3>2. Luxury Fitness Brand is Bringing Never Before Seen Concepts to the Industry This Holiday Season</h3>
<h2><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/f7a7a184-6700-45e2-b4e3-2e345ca760d6_Screenshot202021-02-0820at2010.53.38.png" alt="Luxury Fitness Brand Is Bringing Never Before Seen Concepts to the Industry This Holiday Season" width="1600" height="417" /></h2>
<p>This headline is timely in that it‚Äôs about a specific time of the year, but it also piques curiosity by promising something ‚Äúnever seen before‚Äù. Journalists will likely want to know what those unique concepts are and click through to have a look.</p>
<h3>3. U.S. Median Home Asking Prices Hit a New High, Up 10% From Last Year</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/c6f8c0c4-d6a5-4257-9e8a-c1e9b07cfac6_Screenshot202021-02-0820at2010.55.45.png" alt="U.S. Median Home Asking Prices Hit a New High, Up 10% From Last Year" width="1418" height="490" /></p>
<p>Using numbers or percentages in headlines can give them the extra spice they need to stand out in an inbox full of words.</p>
<h3>4. Myanmar: Internet blackout a ‚Äòheinous and reckless decision‚Äô</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/ce3cdbbd-104c-455e-9a92-bb90dd8cb905_Screenshot202021-02-0820at2012.36.58.png" alt="Myanmar: Internet blackout a 'heinous and reckless decision'" width="1184" height="554" /></p>
<p>This press release headline combines incredibly emotive words with a quote from the release itself. The powerful wording choices will, no doubt, compel journalists to find out more.</p>
<h3>5. While Many Companies Are Laying Off Employees, Raleigh-Based Software Company Persistence AI is Hiring Hundreds for Its New Product</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/d46c0e45-0205-49fd-aa48-677e1c3f9fbc_Screenshot202021-02-0820at2013.40.09.png" alt="While many companies are laying off employees, Raleigh-based software company Persistence AI is hiring hundreds for its new product " width="1600" height="569" /></p>
<p>While this is a pretty lengthy press release headline, it does the job. It tells readers exactly what the release is about by using simple language that‚Äôs also relevant for the current times.</p>
<h3>6. 7taps to Turn Corporate Learning into Instagramming, Bringing an Unprecedented 99% Course-Completion Rate</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="drop-shadow alignnone" src="https://media.coschedule.com/uploads/2021/04/f5fa4f10-d068-4381-abae-69c76c269689_Screenshot202021-02-0820at2014.02.42.png" alt="7taps to turn corporate learning into Instagramming, bringing an unprecedented 99% course-completion rate" width="1600" height="522" /></p>
<p>This headline uses both numbers (in a percentage format) and emotional language, like the word ‚ÄúUnprecedented‚Äù. It begins by sharing what the company is doing and what the outcome is from doing it.</p>
<h2>Make Sure Your Press Releases Are Read By Using Irresistible Headlines</h2>
<p>Press releases are an important opportunity for your business. They have the chance to propel your brand and its current news into the limelight ‚Äî generating more eyeballs, more traffic and, ultimately, more sales.</p>
